"```sql\nSELECT MAX(monthly_consumption) AS biggest_monthly_consumption\nFROM (\n    SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) / 12 AS monthly_consumption\n    FROM yearmonth y\n    JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID\n    WHERE c.Currency = 'EUR'\n    GROUP BY y.CustomerID\n) AS customer_monthly_consumption;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the biggest monthly consumption for customers who use euro as their currency. It first calculates the monthly consumption for each customer by summing their consumption over the year and dividing by 12. Then, it finds the maximum of these monthly consumption values."